text.section:
To engage in business as a premium finance company in the State, each premium finance company shall elect to:
maintain a net worth of at least $250,000 calculated under generally accepted accounting principles;
file with the Commissioner an irrevocable letter of credit in the amount of $50,000 issued by a financial institution;
deposit with the State Treasurer cash in the amount of $50,000; or
file with the Commissioner a bond that:
is in favor of the State;
is in the penal sum of $50,000;
is executed by an authorized surety insurer; and
is conditioned that the premium finance company will account for and pay over to the person entitled to receive it all money belonging to the person that comes into the possession of the premium finance company, including unearned premiums due to an insured and unearned commissions due to an insurer.
